SUMMARY:Economic Theory – David Delacretaz (UManchester) – Simultaneous
  Processing in Multi-Prioity Systems
LOCATION:Room 304\, FBE Building\, 111 Barry St\, Carlton VIC 3053
DESCRIPTION:David Delacretaz: “Simultaneous Processing in Multi-Prioity S
 ystems”\nhttps://daviddelacretaz.net/\n\nGoogle Maps: https://maps.app.g
 oo.gl/BirLkJKurX9pSbBB8\n\nABSTRACT:\nPolicymakers frequently use multi-pr
 iority systems to combine competing objectives in allocating a scarce reso
 urce. In a multi-priority system\, the capacity is split across several ca
 tegories that implement different priorities. The order in which categorie
 s are processed impacts the outcome and has led to unintended consequences
 . I introduce a new solution\, which handles all categories simultaneously
 . I characterize my solution\, showing that it satisfies basic desiderata 
 and is category neutral: If an agent qualifies for n categories\, she take
 s 1/n units from each. A practical advantage is that the categories’ rel
 ative importance is captured by the amount of capacity they allocate.
END:VEVENT
