SUMMARY:PhD Brown Bag Seminar – Yobin Timilsena (University of Melbourne)
  – Spatial Transmission of Inequality in Education
LOCATION:Room 304\, FBE Building\, 111 Barry St\, Carlton VIC 3053
DESCRIPTION:Yobin Timilsena: “Spatial Transmission of Inequality in Educa
 tion”\n\nGoogle Maps: https://maps.app.goo.gl/BirLkJKurX9pSbBB8\n\nABSTR
 ACT:\nThis project explores how spatial differences in education quality c
 ontribute to persistent inequality. I build a spatial overlapping generati
 ons model where households make location and education decisions that shap
 e long-run outcomes. Education quality varies across space and is influenc
 ed by school funding\, neighbourhood composition\, and associated spatial 
 spillovers. Using Australian data\, I aim to quantify the role of these fa
 ctors in driving inequality in education quality and assess the impact of 
 policy interventions such as funding equalization and improved school acce
 ss.
END:VEVENT
